<subSubSection id="B7C8652BFFA07A08FF18FBA9FBE8AFF3" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FF6D36A0FFA07A08FF18FBA9FD59AF43" blockId="2.[151,1437,258,1255]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis id="CDA6EAB2FFA07A08FF18FBA9FEC2AF27" bold="true" box="[199,315,1050,1075]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="20698802FFA07A08FEA7FBA9FE23AF27" box="[376,474,1050,1075]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">holotype</typeStatus>
and the 
<typeStatus id="20698802FFA07A08FD9FFBA8FD59AF27" box="[576,672,1051,1075]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">paratype</typeStatus>
(slightly teneral specimen with one of the wings damaged) do not bear any label regarding the date of collection.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF6D36A0FFA07A08FF18FBD0FBE8AFF3" blockId="2.[151,1437,258,1255]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">
<taxonomicName id="38D24D23FFA07A08FF18FBD0FEBBAF6F" box="[199,322,1123,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mahellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cardoni">
<emphasis id="CDA6EAB2FFA07A08FF18FBD0FEBBAF6F" box="[199,322,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">M. cardoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="38D24D23FFA07A08FE1EFBD0FD1DAF6F" authority="Distant" authorityName="Distant" box="[449,740,1122,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Jassus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="determinatus">
<emphasis id="CDA6EAB2FFA07A08FE1EFBD0FD81AF6F" box="[449,632,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">M. determinatus</emphasis>
(Distant)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="87C57630FFA07A08FCF7FBD1FC59AF6F" box="[808,928,1122,1147]" name="Seychelles" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Seychelles</collectingCountry>
in having similar male genitalia. However, it differs from the latter in the following characters (characters of 
<taxonomicName id="38D24D23FFA07A08FCAEFB34FBD3AF8A" box="[881,1066,1158,1182]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Jassus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="determinatus">
<emphasis id="CDA6EAB2FFA07A08FCAEFB34FBD3AF8A" box="[881,1066,1158,1182]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">M. determinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in parenthesis): subgenital plate more or less of uniform width throughout with apex rounded (of uneven width and apex truncate); the style with apical half abruptly narrowed into thin process (apical 1/4 gradually narrowed).
</paragraph>
